[[File:Johann Heinrich Wilhelm Krombach 01.png|right|thumb|<center>Jean-Henri-Guillaume Krombach]] '''Jean-Henri-Guillaume Krombach''', also known as '''Johann Heinrich Wilhelm Krombach''' (16 September 1791 in [[Moers]] &ndash; 23 February 1881 in [[Luxembourg City]]) was a German-Luxembourgian [[pharmacist]] and [[botanist]].
He initially worked as an assistant pharmacist in a number of German cities ([[Soest, Germany|Soest]], [[Mainz]] and [[Aachen]]), then in 1815 relocated as a pharmacist to [[Diekirch]], Luxembourg.<ref name=BH>[https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/33068920 BHL] Taxonomic literature : a selective guide to botanical publications</ref> From 1850 he served as a pharmacist in the nearby town of [[Ettelbruck]].<ref name=NN>[http://ssm.lu/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/1939.1.pdf 1939.1 - Société des Sciences Médicales]</ref>
Beginning in 1830 he taught classes in natural sciences at schools in Diekirch and Ettelbruck.<ref name=BH/><ref name=NN/> In 1871 he was named president of the Société de botanique du Grand-Duché de Luxembourg.<ref>[http://www.snl.lu/publications/bulletin/SNL_1990_091_005_214.pdf La Société des Naturalistes Luxembourgeois]</ref>
In 1875, he published "''Flore du grand-duché de Luxembourg. Plantes phanérogames''" (Flora of the [[Grand Duchy of Luxembourg]]; [[phanerogam]]s).<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/flore-du-grand-duche-de-luxembourg-plantes-phanerogames/oclc/18116182 Flore du grand-duché de Luxembourg] OCLC WorldCat</ref> He is the [[taxonomic authority]] of the [[Tribe (biology)|subtribe]] Olyrinae (family [[Poaceae]]).<ref>[https://www.gbif.org/species/103038210 Olyrinae Kromb.] GBIF</ref> {{Botanist|Kromb.|Krombach, Jean-Henri-Guillaume}}
